column5: I will take  a morning of small smallies anytime.  Lots of action on the tube and I think I beat or atleast tied, last years PB. . ( team ones going to hate me for this, no sign.)  Arrived to morning west winds, but the call of changing to the south 6 k made me fish this spot. Didnt take long for the west to die.     Throwing the spinner bait searching for active fish, but none to be found. I found that odd in this one spot. Tie on my favorite tube and what ya know, they just wanted something to drop right in front of thier face. Lazy buggers.  Probly hooked into a dozen of them and lost a few others.        It was sock washing day.LOL    Nasty.     The lake calmed down so headed out to the drop off to try some jigging. Marked some fish , a lone juvie herring was all that was offered up.    . Oh that south wind they called for, really was from the east. Go figure.  So decided to head back in and play with the smallies again. This is where I am watching the graph and seeing fish zooming off the bottom and up to about the 5 foot mark in 18 fow. Active fish. I decide to start throwing the spinner bait. 2nd cast and it,s on. This fish comes rocketing out of the water. No no, Im going to lose it. Down it goes only to come rocketing out again. Im like OMG come on. Finaly get it to the toon and it wants to dive again. I grab the net and out it rockets again right in front of me. I just heaved back the pole and got it in the net. Long and fat. Picture does not do justice for this fish. It was pushing high 6,s for sure. My previous one was short and real chunky. Not easy to compare them, but holding it, I could tell.
Good going B. Send that fish to NASA they are having a bad time with their 'rockets'. And a LEW smile to boot!
Nicely done Brian,looked like a nice morning.
Nice smalljaw!!!  Frig im envious of that 'toon?
Way to go B, a nice Sunday morning for sure  Did you wash all the socks?
Thanks gang.    I been hearing rumbling theres no fish in this lake.  Frig im envious of that 'toon  When I was heading home, I drove by the tiffen launch. Lined up to the road.
Thats hilarious brian.  Seriously I wanna buy a toon.  Sooooo many possibilities up here.  And it just looks awesome?

nice going  great smallie  I got it out on that flat I have been telling you about. This weekend we,ll get out there bud, No you cannot fish it before then.   I also found that spot we talked about during the hard water season. It,s a lot further out then I thought. LOL
Didn't know that stinkbait works for smallies B  Just kidding lol.  Beauty smallie, the big ones fight so hard.
